articles.title: Scott Morrison 'deliberately deceived France' with sub deal, Malcolm Turnbull says - SBS News
articles.description: Former prime minister Malcolm Turnbull warns the repercussions from tearing up a submarine contract with France is likely to “dog our relations with Europe for years”.
articles.content:
Australia scrapped a $90 billion contract with French company Naval Group in favour of exploring nuclear-powered submarines in a deal with the United Kingdom and the United States.
The decision sunk… [+2568 chars]
